## 🎯 What's MISSING — High-Impact Features to Add

Based on market research, Reddit user feedback, and competitor analysis, here are the **top features ranked by purchase-driving impact**:

---

### 🥇 #1 — Pre-Built Workout Programs / Templates (HIGHEST IMPACT)

**Why it sells:** This is the **#1 reason** people pay for gym apps. Most people don't know what routine to follow. Providing **ready-to-go, structured programs** is the single biggest value-add.

**What to add:**
- **15-20 pre-built programs** covering popular routines:
  - 🏋️ **Push/Pull/Legs (PPL)** — 3-day & 6-day splits
  - 💪 **Upper/Lower Split** — 4-day program
  - 🔥 **Full Body 3x/Week** — Beginner-friendly
  - 📈 **5/3/1 Wendler** — Strength-focused
  - 🎯 **PHUL** (Power Hypertrophy Upper Lower)
  - 🏃 **Beginner Starting Strength** — For newbies
  - 🏠 **Home Workout (No Equipment)** — Bodyweight only
  - 💥 **HIIT Strength Hybrid** — Fat loss + muscle
  - 🎽 **Bro Split** — Classic 5-day
- Each program includes:
  - Week-by-week structure
  - Exercise order, sets, reps, rest times pre-filled
  - Progressive overload suggestions
  - "Start This Program" → auto-populates daily workouts

> [!TIP]
> **Market insight:** Apps like JEFIT and Hevy charge $40-80/year largely for this feature. Offering it at $2.99 one-time is an **incredible value proposition** — use this as your main selling point in app store marketing.

---

### 🥈 #2 — Personal Records (PR) Tracking & Celebrations

**Why it sells:** Dopamine hits. Users LOVE seeing "🎉 NEW PR!" notifications. This is the #1 feature users mention in positive reviews of Strong and Hevy.

**What to add:**
- Auto-detect PRs for each exercise (1RM, best volume, heaviest set)
- **PR celebration screen** with confetti animation
- PR history timeline per exercise
- Estimated 1RM calculator (Epley/Brzycki formulas)
- "PR Board" screen showing all-time bests

---

### 🥉 #3 — Workout Streak & Gamification System

**Why it sells:** Retention = reviews = organic downloads. The #1 way users discover paid apps is through **word of mouth and app store ratings**.

**What to add:**
- 🔥 **Workout streak counter** (consecutive workout days/weeks)
- 🏆 **Achievement badges:**
  - "First Workout", "10 Workouts", "50 Workouts", "100 Workouts"
  - "Bench Press 100kg", "Squat 2x Bodyweight"
  - "30-Day Streak", "Early Bird" (workout before 7am)
  - "Variety King" (10 different exercises in one week)
- 📊 **Weekly/Monthly summary cards** (shareable to social media)
- Streak protection ("rest day" allowance)

---

### 🏅 #4 — Superset / Circuit / Giant Set Support

**Why it sells:** This is the **most-requested missing feature** in competitor apps. Most gym trackers only support straight sets. Advanced lifters need this.

**What to add:**
- Link exercises together as supersets (A1/A2)
- Circuit mode (cycle through 3+ exercises)
- Giant sets support
- Auto-advance between linked exercises
- Rest timer only triggers after completing the full superset

---

### 🏅 #5 — Workout Notes & Body Measurements

**Why it sells:** Users want a **complete fitness journal**, not just a set logger.

**What to add:**
- Per-exercise notes (e.g., "felt strong today", "left shoulder sore")
- Body measurement tracking:
  - Neck, chest, waist, hips, biceps, thighs, calves
  - Progress photos (before/after gallery)
  - Measurement graphs over time
- Mood/energy rating per workout (1-5 scale)

---

### 🏅 #6 — Dark Mode + Multiple Themes

**Why it sells:** This is surprisingly one of the top filters people use in gym app reviews. "No dark mode = instant uninstall" is a real sentiment.

**What to add:**
- Proper dark mode (AMOLED black option)
- 3-4 theme options (Dark, Light, AMOLED Black, Blue Steel)
- Auto dark mode based on system settings

---

### 🏅 #7 — Data Backup & Restore

**Why it sells:** The #1 fear users have with one-time purchase apps is **losing their data**. This removes purchase hesitation.

**What to add:**
- Export/Import full backup as JSON file
- Google Drive / iCloud backup integration
- Auto backup scheduling (weekly)

---

## 📣 Marketing Strategy to Hit 957 Sales

### App Store Optimization (ASO) — FREE

| Element | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| **Title** | "Gym Log - Workout Tracker & Programs" |
| **Subtitle** | "No subscription. One-time purchase." |
| **Keywords** | gym tracker, workout log, no subscription, one time purchase, lifting tracker, strength training |
| **Screenshots** | Show: Programs, PR celebration, Streak, Plate calculator, Progress charts |
| **Description** | Lead with "NO SUBSCRIPTION EVER" — this is your #1 differentiator |

### Pricing Psychology

> [!TIP]
> **$2.99 one-time price is your superpower.** Competitors charge $40-80/year. Position yourself as: *"Everything Hevy/Strong charge monthly for — but you pay ONCE."*

### Marketing Channels (Low/No Cost)

1. **Reddit** (r/fitness, r/gym, r/weightroom, r/bodybuilding)
   - Post genuine "I built this" threads — Reddit loves indie devs
   - The "no subscription" angle gets MASSIVE upvotes on Reddit
   
2. **TikTok/YouTube Shorts**
   - Quick 15-sec demos of: PR celebrations, workout programs, plate calculator
   - Gym influencer partnerships (micro-influencers, 5-50K followers)

3. **App Store Reviews**
   - Prompt for reviews after milestones (10th workout, first PR)
   - High ratings = more organic discovery

4. **Twitter/X Fitness Community**
   - Launch thread: "I spent X months building a gym tracker that costs $2.99 once — no subscription ever"

